Partly cloudy- wind east-southeast at 5 knots.
Lots of boat activity yesterday (4th of July holiday).  Boats stirred up lake.  Wind SE at 8 knots.
SE wind- hazy- and first noticeable algae.
Light north breeze- sunny- and noted Department of Natural Resource's person in nearby boat doing various water tests at same time.
Light southwest breeze- air temperature is 102 degrees- and clear skies.
Clear but hazy skies (no clouds)- south-southwest breeze 6-8 mph and the temperature is 104 degrees.
Northwest wind at 8-10 mph and clear skies.
Northwest wind at five mph and clear skies.
Light southerly breeze and clear skies.
SE breeze approximately 10 mph and recorded 3.6" of rain previous 24 hours.
Partly cloudy and most geese using lake.  There is no secchi depth given.
Clear- 8-10 mph southerly wind and the temperature is 78 degrees.
North wind- partly sunny- light chop- ice off April 4th and lake level that date was 827.9'.

High northerly wind this past week prevented accurate readings.  However today water was calm and sun was hazy but bright.  The 28.5 reading startled me so I brought two neighbors back to check resources.  Both confirmed!!
Water very calm and sun hazy.  Drifted over 15'-20' deep and could watch fish swimming on the bottom.  Beautiful!
Moderate northwest breeze and sunny at time of reading.  Newspaper reported with me because he wanted to do story on water clarity.
Breezy- NE wind and water has a very light greenish yellow tone compared to previous week (this Sunday report much large boat activity).
SE breeze- green algae bloom and the water is between a blue and green color.
Clear with light NW breeze.  Heavy holiday boat traffic- lake level continues to drop.
Overcast- NE light breeze- choppy surface and green algae.
Hazy skies- southerly 12-15 knot wind and algae level is high.
Clear sky- light SW breeze- heavy green algae- large concentrations of very large Bluegills suspended at 20' in 50-60' water.  Many fishermen enjoying.
Southerly breeze at 10 mph and cloudy.
Wind southerly at 15 mph and clear sky.
Light northerly breeze and clear skies.  Algae bloom (color olive) decreased clarity.
Southwest wind at 10-12 mph- lake choppy- skies clear- ice out 3/20/90 and lake level that day was 828.4.
Southwest breeze at 10-12 mph and clear skies.
Very warm. Southerly wind at 10-15 mph and clear skies.
Brown algae staining the water- as bad as we've seen.  Would not swim in it.  Northwest breeze and partly cloudy.
We have large amounts of green algae growing along our shorelines- coating bottom and also floating.  People on south shore are complaining.  Partly clear and steady wind.
SE wind at 10-15 mph- hazy and blue green algae bloom extremely heavy.
West wind at 8 mph- overcast and still have filamentous algae in large areas along south and west shoreline.
North wind is quite strong at 12-15 K- partly sunny and algae bloom easing up a bit.
South brisk breeze and partly sunny.
Light overcast skies- water choppy- south breeze and continued above normal algae concentrations.
Wind is southwest at 10-15 mph and slight haze.  No received rain gauge this date- so no record to data.
South wind at 10-12 mph- sunny but slight haze- another algae bloom clouding water- blooms more frequent than past few years.
South wind at 8-10 mph and partly cloudy.
South wind at 8-10 mph and partly cloudy.
Southwest wind at 6-8 mph- and partly sunny.  1.45" of rain from 7/18-8/16.  On 7/28 = 0.95" of rain- 7/29 = 0.30" of rain- 8/10 = 0.15" of rain- and on 8/12 = 0.05" of rain.
Slight east wind- hazy- partly sunny and lake quite turbid as we received excess of 6" of rainfall past weekend.
Wind calm- partly cloudy and the water is tinted yellow green in color.
Hazy- partly clear and lake calm.
Clear skies- warm- light SW breeze (took extended samples this day also) lake has turned over and dissolved oxygen practically constant from top to bottom. (59').  8.65" of rain from 8/16-9/26.
Strong SW winds and clear skies.
Southwest breeze 5-8 mph- clear skies after three days of high winds and snowstorm yesterday.
RUN LOW LEVEL P UNLESS  more than  .2 MG/L
West winds at 10-15 mph and partly sunny.
Light SW breeze and slightly hazy.  Best clarity in two years.
South breeze- calm- great water clarity and clear skies.
Light SE breeze- surface choppy and clear skies.
SE wind at 6-8 mph- hazy- partly overcast and water level and great clarity constant for over one month!
The lake is calm and clear skies.
Partly cloudy- lake calm- ideal for reading disc- light algae bloom but still excellent clarity.
Light south breeze and clear skies.
West breeze at 5 mph- clear skies and lake has a light chop.
Partly cloudy- SW wind at 8-10 mph- light algae bloom (green)- water turbid from violent storm last week plus heavy boat traffic.
Clear skies- west breeze at 6-8 mph and light algae bloom.
Overcast- dark sky- 5-7 mph east breezy and medium algae.  The rain gauge reading from 7/5-8/5 is 2.4 inches.
West breeze at 5-10 mph and partly cloudy.
Hot- partly cloudy- 1-3 mph north wind and moderate algae bloom.
Clear skies and west 3-5 mph breeze.
East wind at 10 mph- overcast skies and Gus- representative from the Department of Natural Resources- worked tests with us.  Rain gauge reading from 8/5-9/10 is 2.9 inches.
South breeze at 5-8 mph and clear skies.
Algae level reduced clarity to lowest level (8.25) of the season.  Partly cloudy and north light breeze.
Cloudy- southwest wind at 5-8 mph- poor clarity- results possible because lake in process of turning over.  Rain gauge reading from 9/10-9/30 is 4.27 inches
Light north breeze- overcast with occasional showers- water clarity low- probably because lake currently in process of turning over.
South winds at 5-8 mph and partly cloudy.
Wind is 15 mph from the south and partly cloudy.  Rain gauge reading from 9/30-10/23 is 0.7 inches.
Hazy sky and south winds at 10-15 mph.
Calm- no wind- and clear skies.
South wind at 10-15 mph and hazy skies.
Calm lake surface and clear skies.
Northwest wind at 6-8 mph and partly cloudy.
Light south breeze at 5-7 mph- clear skies- hot and new algae blooms.
Calm- partly cloudy and algae level increasing.
Light breeze from southeast at 3-5 mph and clear skies.
South breeze at 3 mph and overcast.
South breeze at 3-5 mph and clear skies.
Overcast- light chop and west breeze at 1-3 mph.
Partly cloudy and the lake is calm.
Partly cloudy- light breeze from the north.  Rain gauge reading from 7/1-7/31 is 8.9 inches.
Partly cloudy with 3-5 mph breeze- continued algae presence.  Rain gauge from 8/11 to 8/24 is 1.35 inches.
Clear and east breeze at 3-6 mph.
North breeze at 3-5 mph and partly cloudy.
Partly cloudy- cold- lake mixing.  The rain gauge reading from 8/24-9/30 is 5.8 inches.
Clear skies and light south breeze.
Light north breeze (almost calm) and clear skies.
6" of rain previous 48 hours- hazy skies- SE wind 6-8 mph.
Partly cloudy skies- SE wind 10-15 mph
W winds 15-18 mph- clear skies- algae bloom reducing visibility.
North-northwest wind @ 6-10 mph- skies are partly cloudy.
Water perfectly calm under clear skies.
Windy- partly cloudy- high algae levels.
Light southerly breeze and clear skies.
Starting wind from the south @ 5 mph- increasing to 15 miles per hour by the end of sampling.
Calm- clear and cold.  This is the worst secchi disk reading in years.
Southwest breeze @ 7-10 mph- clear skies.  The current algae bloom is most severe have ever seen.  Secchi depth is the poorest we have ever reported.  The water is very brown.
Calm- no wind- clear skies- with clarity @ 21'- motored all over the lake- exploring the bottom - wonderful!
Hot humid- southerly winds @ 8-12 mph- partly cloudy.
Water calm- partly sunny - heaviest green algal bloom of the season.
Heavy algal bloom- partly sunny- south wind @ 10-15 mph.
Perfectly calm- no breeze- sunny skies.
South westerly breeze @ 5 mph- unseasonably warm - sunny skies
Green algae bloom- SE breeze- hazy skies.
South winds- 5-8 mph- partly cloudy- hot!  Swimmer's itch common.
Hazy- hot- calm water- 90 degrees- algae levels continue- high.
Hot- 90 degrees- clear skies- westerly wind @ 10-12 mph.
Winds from west @ 5 mph- clear skies.
Overcast sky- windy- NW wind @ 10 to 14 mph- slight brown algae present.
West winds at 15-18 mph- clear skies.
Lake reaching highest level in year.  Piers underwater or broken up.
Water capacity terrible due to heavy rains and runoff. level of lake highest in year.
Lake high and dirty from record rains.
Clarity limited from heavy rain (runoff) and algae.
Partly cloudy- sly wind @ 10-12 mph- temperature is continuous.
Clear skies- water calm- green algae bloom
Lake was calm- southwest  winds 5 mph- partly cloudy
Overcast- with west winds at 8-10 mph- lakes turning over
30 boats with an average of 2 in each boat. Conducted tests wrong for D.O.

DEEP HOLE     50% cloud cover; wind speed 20mph from S; site depth 58ft; Algae development = slight (just visible); Depth of Integrated Water Sample = 6ft; SLH Field Number = RO; Amount filtered for chlorophyll = 190mls

DEEP HOLE - INTEGRATED SAMPLER     "deep hole"; 100% Light Rain; Graham/Albert Observers; wind 3mph from SW; secchi 8.0 (feet/meters not marked); Algae Development = Slight- just visible; Custer color Strip Reading = 2; Site depth 50 (ft/meters not marked; assume ft); Depth of integrated water sample = 9ft; SLH Field Number = ROI
100%/0%precip; wind 5mph from SW; custer color strip reading = 2; algae development - slight (just visible); chlorophyll - unfiltered to lab; SLH Field number RI1 + RI2; site depth 45ft
Partly cloudy- 4-7 mph breeze from west southwest- small wavelets. Small particles algae present. 20 dead hand sized blue gills near site. Very high water- slow no wake in force.

Sunny- 0-5mph breeze out of northwest- 78F. Ripples to wavelets. Same amount of small pieces of algae as 6/7. Lake water still very high- down 1 to 2 inches from 6/7. Only one dead pan fish noted. Small amount of foam along Bartel beach.
Wind out of northwest- 5-7 mph- 75 F.- sunny to partly cloudy. Slow no wake restriction removed 6/23/04. Lake level down but still high for this time of year. Same aount of small algae as last time.

Oil slick at site of measurement. Sunny- 3 to 5 mph breeze from north northwest. Wavelets. Lake is still high for this time of the year. Two speed boats and 18 fishing boats noted on the water. Greatest number seen so far this season.
Mid 60's. Gentle breeze. Small waves. Overcast.

partly cloudy- began to drizzle while on lake- small waves; long-term trends + QA/QC check for volunteer
Water surface temp. 46F- light winds- partly cloudy
sunny- 75 degrees- saw 2 loons- some green algae near shore
Wind calm- water surface temp 68F- sunny
Winds calm- sunny- water surface temperture 76F

column2: 74 degrees- partly cloudy- some suspended algae- saw loons in the morning

Sunny- Ambient temp ~ 65 degrees F 0% cloud cover Depth finder- 60.8 ft 4 boats @ CTH B ramp water very clear *Note: Secchi- Temp.- DO- pH- and Conductivity form was chosen because SECCHI_TEMPDO form only allows up to 15 entries and there are 20 entries for this particular sample.
Sunny- light wind- water surface temperature 74F.
some suspended algae- mid-80s- partly cloudy
partly sunny- low 70s- windy- suspended algae

Weather was overcast and around 65 degrees F.  There was suspended algae in the water.  I was unable to exactly get to the deep hole.  Therefore- the temp + do information is only to 30 feet of depth.
Located deep hole with a depth finder at 62-64 feet- and marked the location as:
partly cloudy- ~84F- humid- some suspended algae-

too windy to get accurate secchi reading
boat may have drifted off deep hole during the temp/do profile

column2: 86 degrees F; windy- leading to drifting of boat; overcast
Only tested temp + do to see if lake was turned over.

column1: conductivity = 280 uS/cm assisted by Scott Erwin
partly sunny- lots of rain in the past week

assisted by Steve Oostdik- 85F- sunny- surface conductivity = 391 uS/cm
Air temperature 57 degrees F- partly cloudy- windy. Carinna Kroll and Scott Erwin assisted. Conductivity=450 uS
Wind picked  up a lot. Good weather. Clouds 30%. Winds 10-15 NE. Air 82F. Had volunteers in boat (Bud and Nick).
Assisted by Steve and Hope Oostdik.

Cold (43 F)- but wind was only at 9mph so not too bad. Saw 4 loons in the south end of the lake. Two more were spotted when we were closer to the north end- so probably not the same. We used Patricia's DO/temp meter.
Air tem 70F- overcast- wind about 10 MPH

column1: the temperature + DO meter would not calibrate.

column2: Air temperature 75F- 0% cloud cover- wind estimated at 3mph. Very calm and beautiful.

Also assisted by Bob Volenec who took us out in his boat for monitoring today. Chilly and breezy- but over all a beautiful day. Cloud cover about 35%- Air temp. 11.7 C. Wind 10-15 mph.  The water level is slightly high for this time of year- above the range for management of the dam.  Patricia checked staff gauge and will add that data in her data entry. I accidently read off the DO % saturation instead of mg/L. After getting the barometric pressure for the 1-2pm hour from Sullivan weather station staff- I was able to convert to mg/L using a USGS conversion tool. This method was not a sensitive as the probe. The original data is available.  (Jeanne)
